racter','Rebel','2','2','3','4','When at a war room you control, adds 1 to power of each Rebel starship at the related system. May use 1 Force to cancel Astromech Shortage.','Leader of Rebel forces on Yavin 4. Formerly Suolriep sector HQ commander. As a Rebel spy, aided Princess Leia and Bail Organa in the years prior to the Senate\'s dissolution.',NULL,'2_5'),(1815,5443,'Light','U2','Virtual Set 11','•Commander Vanden Willard (V)','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Virtual11-Light/large/commandervandenwillard.gif?raw=true','Character','Rebel','2','2','2','4','Alderaanian. Once per game, may place your just lost Alderaanian in Used Pile. Once per turn, if Stolen Data Tapes \'delivered,\' a system \'liberated,\' or Stardust on your spy, may place a card from hand on Used Pile to draw top card of Reserve Deck.','Leader of Rebel forces on Yavin 4. Formerly Suolriep sector HQ commander. As a Rebel spy, aided Princess Leia and Bail Organa in the years prior to the Senate\'s dissolution.',NULL,'211_58'),(1816,506,'Light','R','Special Edition','•Commander Wedge Antilles','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/SpecialEdition-Light/large/commanderwedgeantilles.gif?raw=true','Character','Rebel','3','3','3','6','Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Rogue 3, also adds 2 to maneuver and draws battle destiny if not able to otherwise. May use 2 Force to take one One More Pass into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.','Promoted to commander for his heroism in the Battle of Yavin. Leader in charge of training new pilots assigned to Echo Base. Piloted Rogue 3 in the battle of Hoth.',NULL,'7_12'),(1817,5125,'Light','R','Virtual Set 5','•Commander Wedge Antilles (V)','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Virtual5-Light/large/commanderwedgeantilles.gif?raw=true','Character','Rebel','3','3','3','6','Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. While piloting Rogue 3, it is maneuver +2 and your Force drains here are +1. While piloting a T-47, Wedge draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise and, if opponent draws more than one battle destiny here, may cancel one.','Promoted to commander for his heroism in the Battle of Yavin. Leader in charge of training new pilots assigned to Echo Base. Piloted Rogue 3 in the battle of Hoth.',NULL,'205_1'),(1818,507,'Light','C','Endor','•Commando Training','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Endor-Light/large/commandotraining.gif?raw=true','Effect',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deploy on your side of table. Each of your non-unique Rebels armed with a non-unique blaster is forfeit +2, adds 1 to his total weapon destiny and, where present, cumulatively adds 1 to total battle destiny. (Immune to Alter while your non-unique blaster is on table.)','Han\'s Rebel strike team on the forest moon of Endor was highly trained in the use of blasters and explosives.',NULL,'8_36'),(1819,509,'Light','R2','A New Hope','•Commence Recharging','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/ANewHope-Light/large/commencerecharging.gif?raw=true','Effect',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deploy on a superlaser. May not fire at a planet until \'recharged.\' Opponent may use Force (stacking it here); accumulating 8 Force recharges superlaser. When fired at a planet, Effect is canceled. If Effect canceled, accumulated Force is placed in Used Pile.','The huge strain on the little-tested power generator matrix of the superlaser\'s fusion reactor can require full recharging before the system can be used again.',NULL,'2_31'),(1820,511,'Light','C','Cloud City','Computer Interface','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/CloudCity-Light/large/computerinterface.gif?raw=true','Interrupt','Used Or Lost','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,'USED: Cancel Limited Resources.  LOST: Use 2 Force (free if Lobot on table) to examine the top card of your Reserve Deck, Force Pile and Used Pile. Return one of those three cards to the top of each deck or pile.\"','Lobot\'s direct link with the Cloud City central computer allowed him to efficiently manipulate the floating city\'s resources.',NULL,'5_40'),(1821,514,'Light','R','Death Star II','•Concentrate All Fire','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/DeathStarII-Light/large/concentrateallfire.gif?raw=true','Admiral\'s Order',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Each starfighter that fires a weapon in battle is power +3 for the remainder of battle. Once per turn you may cancel and redraw your starship weapon destiny just drawn. At sites related to systems you occupy, your characters who have immunity to attrition each add 2 to immunity and 1 to each of that character\'s weapon destiny draws.',NULL,'Fighter Cover','9_3'),(1822,515,'Light','R1','Hoth','Concussion Grenade','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Hoth-Light/large/concussiongrenade.gif?raw=true','Weapon','Character','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Use 2 Force to deploy on your warrior. May \'throw\' at same or adjacent site. Draw destiny. All characters, weapons and devices with that destiny number present at that site are lost. (Only your warrior is lost if destiny = 0.) Concussion Grenade also lost.','Mier-Lan V-59 grenade. Blows stuff up.',NULL,'3_73'),(1823,517,'Light','C','Death Star II','Concussion Missiles','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/DeathStarII-Light/large/concussionmissiles.gif?raw=true','Weapon','Starship','4',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Use 1 Force to deploy on your bomber, A-wing, freighter, or transport. May target a starship for free. Draw destiny. Add 1 if targetting a starfighter or squadron. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.','Used by veteran smugglers. Defend transports from maneuverable TIE fighters. Frequently used to arm Rebellion transports and freighters.','Concussion Missiles','9_87'),(1824,525,'Light','U','Coruscant','Control','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Coruscant-Light/large/control.gif?raw=true','Interrupt','Lost','2',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cancel Sense or Alter. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel an Immediate or Mobile Effect (even if just deployed), or Force drain.','Qui-Gon\'s sense of control assisted him in his final confrontation with Darth Maul. The ability to heal oneself in battle, mentally and physically, can be a huge advantage.','Control (EP1)','12_57'),(1825,521,'Light','U','Dagobah','Control','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Dagobah-Light/large/control.gif?raw=true','Interrupt','Lost','2',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cancel one Sense or Alter card. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel one Immediate Effect, Mobile Effect or Force drain.','Mystical Jedi power. Covers power of inner mind and body. Allows Jedi to exist in harmony with nature. You must learn this.','Control','4_48'),(1826,523,'Light','PM','Reflections II','Control & Tunnel Vision','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/ReflectionsII-Light/large/control&tunnelvision.gif?raw=true','Interrupt','Lost','1',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cancel one Sense or Alter card. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel one Immediate Effect, Mobile Effect, or Force drain. OR Take one card into hand from Force Pile; reshuffle.',NULL,NULL,'10_4'),(1827,527,'Light','R1','A New Hope','•Corellia','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/ANewHope-Light/large/corellia.gif?raw=true','Location','System','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Light: : Your Falcon and your Corellian corvettes may deploy here as a \'react.\'',NULL,NULL,'2_61'),(1828,528,'Light','U','Special Edition','Corellia Operative','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/SpecialEdition-Light/large/corelliaoperative.gif?raw=true','Character','Rebel','3','1','1','3','While at a Corellia site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is forfeit +1 (and power +1 if your Corellian is on Corellia) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Corellia from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.','Many of the Alliance\'s best engineers are sent to Corellia. The Rebellion maintains a presence on Corellia to ensure and assist in the production of the Alliance\'s starships.',NULL,'7_13'),(1829,529,'Light','C2','A New Hope','•••Corellian','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/ANewHope-Light/large/corellian.gif?raw=true','Character','Alien','3','1','1','3','Once per turn, one weapon or device is deploy -1 onto a Rebel at same site.','Brindy Truchong is a typical female Corellian smuggler. Her goal in Mos Eisley is to find a quick means of providing supplies to the Rebellion.',NULL,'2_6'),(1830,530,'Light','U2','Premiere','Corellian Corvette','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Premiere-Light/large/corelliancorvette.gif?raw=true','Starship','Capital: Corvette','1','5','4','8','May add 3 pilots, 4 passengers and 1 vehicle. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.','Multi-purpose Rebel Blockade Runner. Modular interior designed for troop or cargo transport. 150 meters long. Used by Rebels, pirates, corporations and the Empire.',NULL,'1_140'),(1831,531,'Light','R','Special Edition','•Corellian Engineering Corporation','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/SpecialEdition-Light/large/corellianengineeringcorporation.gif?raw=true','Effect',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deploy on Corellia system. All your freighters are deploy -1 and hyperspeed +1. Also, all your Quad Laser Cannons deploy free and add 2 to each of their weapon destiny draws. Suspended while opponent controls Corellia. (Immune to Alter.)','Only one of the \'Big Three\' starship manufacturers to sell primarily to civilians. CEC employees take great delight in calling their highly modifiable designs \'stock\'.',NULL,'7_56'),(1832,532,'Light','U','Jabba\'s Palace','•Corellian Retort','https://github.com/