rate in coordinated patrols, supporting Rebel ground troops and denying infiltration of key planets.',NULL,'7_107'),(2698,5930,'Light','R','Coruscant','•Supreme Chancellor Valorum (AI)','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Coruscant-Light/large/supremechancellorvalorumai.gif?raw=true','Character','Republic','3','2','4','7','Agendas: justice, order. While in a senate majority, once per turn may use 2 Force to cancel a battle destiny just drawn at another site where you have a Republic Character. Opponent may use X Force; Valorum is politics - X for remainder of turn.','Although Finis Valorum maintains the Galactic Senate\'s ultimate title, his real power is mired by endless bureaucracy, petty corruption, and incessant plotting.',NULL,'12_31'),(2699,5934,'Light','U2','Virtual Set 9','•Taidu Sefla','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/Virtual9-Light/large/taidusefla.gif?raw=true','Character','Rebel','3','2','2','4','When deployed (or just lost), may draw bottom card of Used Pile. During battle, may subtract X (limit 3) from a just drawn weapon or battle destiny, where X = number of your spies out of play. Your spies here are immune to Nevar Yalnal.','Trooper.',NULL,'209_13'),(2700,2367,'Light','PM','Jabba\'s Palace Sealed Deck','Stun Blaster','https://github.com/swccgpc/holotable/blob/master/Images-HT/starwars/JabbasPalaceSealedDeck-Light/large/stunblaster.gif?raw=true','Weapon','Character','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Deploy on your warrior. May target a character or creature (except rancor or Sarlacc) using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Return character (and cards deployed on character) to owner\'s hand if destiny +1 > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +3 > defense value.','Stolen Merr-Sonn blaster. Causes no permanent damage, though efficiently immobilizes its target. Effects are more severe on animals without a thick hide.','Stun Blaster','112_8'),(2701,2350,'Light','C','Theed Palace','•Steady, Steady','https://